<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-19T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-19T13:00:00-05:00" n="384" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10141: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-19T14:00:00-04:00">September 19, 1937—2
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>250. Department has repeated Shanghai’s 728, September 19, 1 p.m.<note n="42" xml:id="d384fn42"><ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_499"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol.
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 499</ref>.</note> to Tokyo
                            with request that Ambassador make immediate representations in regard to
                            the safety of the American Embassy and American nationals at
                                Nanking.<note n="43" xml:id="d384fn43">For report of
                                representations, see memorandum by the Ambassador in Japan,
                                September 20, <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_500"><hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 500</ref>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>